###########################################################################
#  text_underline_word - exercises Lout's @Underline primitive on a       #
#  single word in the middle of a flowing sentence.  Existing snippets    #
#  cover bold / italic / oblique (text_styles.lt), kerning and ligatures, #
#  small-caps synthesis, and old-style figures, but none exercises the    #
#  underline-rule emission path in z53.c (drawn as a horizontal <line>    #
#  or <rect> beneath the run, in the current text-fill colour).           #
###########################################################################

@SysInclude { doc }
@Doc @Text @Begin
@PP
The middle word in this sentence is @Underline { emphasised } using
the {@Code "@Underline"} primitive, while the surrounding text remains
plain.  Underlining inherits the current text colour and font metrics,
so the rule sits one descender-width below the baseline.
@End @Text
